{
  "slug": "air-dry-clay-leaf-impression-bowl",
  "tutorialId": "cmps4fciw0001u8v43gya8zyx",
  "capturedAt": "2026-05-30T09:08:21.077Z",
  "preFix": {
    "title": "Air-Dry Clay Leaf Impression Bowl",
    "subtitle": "A textured slab bowl pressed with real leaves",
    "excerpt": "Roll a slab of air-dry clay, press real leaves into the surface for a natural impressed pattern, then drape the slab over an upturned bowl to form the shape. No kiln needed. PVA sealing protects the finished piece.",
    "sourceNotes": "Technique derived from standard air-dry slab-draping and leaf-impression methods.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "This bowl starts as a flat ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "slab",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "label": "slab",
                    "termId": "cmpe36s030000swv4s0l4c11n"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " of air-dry clay pressed with real leaves to create a beautiful ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "impressed pattern",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "label": "impressed pattern",
                    "termId": "cmps4fch10000u8v43gxh3hdb"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ". Once the leaf marks are in, the slab is draped over an upturned household bowl to give it a gentle, organic curve as it dries. No kiln, no specialist tools, and no wheel experience needed. The finished bowl works well as a decorative dish for keys, jewellery, or dried botanicals.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "suppliesCard",
          "attrs": {
            "tools": [
              {
                "name": "Pottery rolling pin",
                "slug": "pottery-rolling-pin",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Needle tool",
                "slug": "needle-tool",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Fettling knife",
                "slug": "fettling-knife",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Mop brush",
                "slug": "pottery-brush-mop",
                "isOptional": false
              }
            ],
            "materials": [
              {
                "name": "Air-dry clay",
                "slug": "air-dry-clay",
                "quantity": "300 g",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Fresh leaves with strong veins (ivy, oak, bay)",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "3-5 leaves",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "PVA glue",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "small bottle",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Two guide sticks or wooden rulers, 5 mm thick",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "2",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Non-stick baking paper",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "2 sheets",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Upturned household bowl, approx 20 cm diameter",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "1",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Cling film",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "enough to cover the bowl",
                "isOptional": false
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Preparation",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Cover your upturned bowl with a layer of cling film, smoothing out as many wrinkles as you can. This stops the clay sticking and makes it easy to lift away.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Collect 3-5 fresh leaves with clear, raised veins. Wipe off any moisture with a cloth. Flat leaves give cleaner prints; avoid curled or very fragile leaves.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Knead the air-dry clay for 2 minutes until it is soft and smooth with no cracks. Keep unused clay wrapped in its original packaging.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Rolling the slab",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Place the clay on a sheet of non-stick baking paper. Lay a 5 mm guide stick on each side of the clay. Roll with the pottery rolling pin, resting the ends of the pin on the guide sticks, until the slab is an even 5 mm thick throughout.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Aim for a circle or rough oval slightly larger than your upturned bowl former. A 25 cm slab works well for a 20 cm bowl.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pressing in the leaves",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Lay your leaves vein-side down onto the surface of the slab in any arrangement you like. Overlapping leaves or a scattered design both work.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Place a fresh sheet of baking paper over the leaves. Roll firmly over the paper with the rolling pin, pressing the leaves 1-2 mm into the clay. Remove the paper.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Carefully peel each leaf away from the clay. You should see a clear ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "impressed pattern",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "label": "impressed pattern",
                            "termId": "cmps4fch10000u8v43gxh3hdb"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " of veins and leaf edges left behind.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Draping and drying",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Lift the slab (still on its baking paper) and drape it carefully over the cling-filmed upturned bowl. Ease the slab down around the bowl with your hands to create a shallow dish shape. The weight of the clay will settle it naturally; do not press hard.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Trim away ragged edges using the fettling knife. Aim for a tidy, rounded rim roughly 2-3 cm from the edge of the bowl former.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Leave the slab on the former at room temperature for 4-6 hours. Once the clay has reached ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "leather-hard",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "label": "leather-hard",
                            "termId": "cmpb7rmoo00008gv4xfq393tk"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " stage, it holds the bowl shape without support. Lift the clay bowl off gently and place it right-side up on fresh baking paper.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Use the needle tool to smooth any rough patches on the rim. Leave to dry fully at room temperature for at least 2 days. Thicker walls or damp conditions may need 3 days.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Sealing",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "When the bowl is fully dry and pale all the way through, brush on a thin, even coat of PVA diluted with water (1:1) using the mop brush. Work it into the impressed texture.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Allow to dry for 1 hour, then apply a second coat. Two coats give a light satin finish and adequate water resistance for light use.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "This bowl is decorative only. It is not waterproof enough for wet soil, food, or drink.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Variations",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "bulletList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Paint the bowl with acrylic before sealing; the impressed lines remain visible through paint.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Press a single large leaf over the whole slab before draping for a more graphic, single-motif look.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Drape over a flatter plate to make a shallower tray shape rather than a bowl.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Use lace or textured fabric instead of leaves for a different kind of surface pattern.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Chill the clay for 10 minutes before pressing to firm it slightly. Use lighter, even pressure next time.",
                "cause": "Clay was too soft or the leaf was pressed in too deeply",
                "problem": "Leaves tore the clay surface when peeled away"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Cover loosely with a plastic bag for the first 2 hours to slow drying. Keep wall thickness at 5 mm throughout.",
                "cause": "The slab dried too fast or was too thin at the edges",
                "problem": "The slab cracked while draped over the bowl"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Wait until the surface is no longer cool and damp to the touch. Return it to the former and leave another 2 hours.",
                "cause": "It was removed before reaching leather-hard stage",
                "problem": "The bowl lost its shape when lifted off the former"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Smooth the cling film carefully before draping. Light texture on the bowl underside is usually acceptable.",
                "cause": "Cling film had wrinkles that pressed into the clay",
                "problem": "Cling film texture transferred to the underside of the bowl"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
